      sideEffects: "GI effects (nausea, diarrhea, bloating — 20-30% of patients; minimized by slow titration and extended-release formulation), metallic taste, vitamin B12 deficiency with long-term use (10-30% — can cause neuropathy mimicking diabetic neuropathy; check B12 annually), lactic acidosis (exceedingly rare but potentially fatal — risk with renal impairment, hypoxia)",
