    pearls: ["T2DM is a PROGRESSIVE disease: beta-cell function declines ~4% per year regardless of treatment — patients who initially achieve control on metformin alone will eventually need additional agents or insulin; this is disease progression, NOT patient failure","Metformin is first-line for EVERYONE with T2DM unless contraindicated — no hypoglycemia, weight-neutral, inexpensive, extensive safety data; most common reason for discontinuation is GI side effects (try extended-release before abandoning)","HbA1c reflects a 2-3 month average: most heavily weighted toward the recent 2-4 weeks; can be falsely low (hemolytic anemias, blood loss) or falsely high (iron deficiency, splenectomy) — when unreliable, use fructosamine or CGM for glucose assessment","Hypoglycemia from sulfonylureas can be PROLONGED AND SEVERE — lasting hours to days, especially in elderly and renal impairment; patients on sulfonylureas should always carry glucose tablets and wear medical identification","The 'Three Ps' (polyuria, polydipsia, polyphagia) are less dramatic in T2DM than T1DM because the onset is gradual; many T2DM patients are asymptomatic at diagnosis, discovered incidentally on routine blood work","Diabetic foot care is essential: T2DM is the leading cause of non-traumatic lower extremity amputation; peripheral neuropathy prevents pain sensation → unnoticed injuries → infection → ulceration → amputation; daily foot inspection and annual professional examination are critical prevention measures"],
