        correct: 1,
        rationale: "When andexanet alfa is unavailable for factor Xa inhibitor reversal, 4-factor PCC (50 units/kg IV) is the recommended alternative. 4F-PCC provides concentrated coagulation factors (II, VII, IX, X) that can overcome the factor Xa inhibition and restore hemostasis within 15-30 minutes. Idarucizumab is specific to dabigatran and will NOT reverse apixaban. Vitamin K reverses warfarin, not DOACs. Waiting for natural drug clearance is inappropriate in life-threatening ICH."
